Interface IRemoteMessage

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Remote
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    RmiMessage

    public interface IRemoteMessage
extends Remote
    This represents a FIX message exposed through RMI.

      • getFieldObjects

        IField[] getFieldObjects()
                  throws RemoteException
        Returns the complete set of fields in the message.

        Never returns null. If the are no fields an empty array is returned.

        Returns:
        Array of fields in the order in which they appear in the message.
        Throws:
        RemoteException - if a communication-related problem occurs
        See Also:
        getITagValues()

      • getStringFieldValue

        String getStringFieldValue(int tag)
                    throws RemoteException
        Returns the string value of the first instance of a field with the given tag.
        Parameters:
        tag - a tag
        Returns:
        String value or null if no such field is in the message.
        Throws:
        RemoteException - if a communication-related problem occurs

      • getITagValues

        ITagValue[] getITagValues()
                   throws RemoteException
        Returns all message fields as array of name/value pairs.

        The value objects will be of type byte[] if the the field's data type is "Data". Otherwise, the value objects will always be of type String - ie a String representation of the actual data type.

        Never returns null. If the are no fields an empty array is returned.

        Returns:
        Array of tag/values
        Throws:
        RemoteException - if a communication-related problem occurs

      • setStringFieldValue

        void setStringFieldValue(int tag,
                         String value)
                  throws RemoteException
        Sets a field's value in the message.

        If the field with the given tag does not exist, it is added.

        Parameters:
        tag - the field's tag number
        value - the field's value
        Throws:
        RemoteException - if a communication-related problem occurs
